<section xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>50-2203.03</num>
  <heading>Immoderate speed not dependent on legal rate of speed.</heading>
  <text>In any prosecution under § <cite path="§50-2203.01">50-2203.01</cite> or § <cite path="§50-2203.02">50-2203.02</cite>, whether the defendant was driving at an immoderate rate of speed shall not depend upon the rate of speed fixed by law for operating such vehicle.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History">Mar. 3, 1901, ch. 854, § 802(c)</annotation>
    <annotation type="History">June 17, 1935, 49 Stat. 385, ch. 266</annotation>
